@glenn-jocher  Following https://github.com/lukemelas/EfficientNet-PyTorch/pull/88, GPU memory consumption for Swish decreases, if the swish implementation inherits `torch.autograd.Function` (code taken from the same pull request) :

```python
class SwishImplementation(torch.autograd.Function):
    @staticmethod
    def forward(ctx, i):
        result = i * torch.sigmoid(i)
        ctx.save_for_backward(i)
        return result

    @staticmethod
    def backward(ctx, grad_output):
        i = ctx.saved_variables[0]
        sigmoid_i = torch.sigmoid(i)
        return grad_output * (sigmoid_i * (1 + i * (1 - sigmoid_i)))

class MemoryEfficientSwish(nn.Module):
    def forward(self, x):
        return SwishImplementation.apply(x)
```

However, this will increase the training time. If you are still using Swish for some of your experiments and getting out of memory errors, it could be useful.
